The paper deals with the construction of cartograms, which involves geometric and graph-theoretic concepts. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and NP-hardness, which are common topics in cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the manipulation of data values, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the computation of max-flow, which is a common topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
